This year's theme was Around the World and competitors were judged in categories ranging from structural integrity to best meal.

Cans are referred to as 'pixels' by the artists and are built into recognisable sculptures by carefully matching the colours to the real thing, like a digital image or an ancient mosaic.

Creators of the best sculptures were put through to a prestigious world final in New York.

All 65,000 of the cans were donated by the community and the contest attracted around 300 participants.

The first Canstruction contest was conceived in New York in 1992 by Cheri Melillo, a member of the Society of Design Administration.

