Since then it has spread as far as Australia and Hawaii and claimed to provide almost four million meals to hungry families last year.

George Kallas, who brought the contest to Vancouver, said: 'As a child I remember my parents taking food to the needier families in the neighborhood during the holidays, this vision really stuck with me and was one of my real motivations behind bringing the event to Vancouver.

'How perfect is it to merge design, creativity and giving to those in need?'

Some 1.23million tins of food - mostly tuna, salmon and ham - have been handed to the Greater Vancouver Foodbank by the event since 2002.

